
This is the foundation. Almost everything else (services, 
ingress, CRDs, controllers, Skupper resources) builds on 
these same kubectl patterns.


Core Concepts to Internalize:

  * Imperative vs Declarative:

      Imperative: kubectl run, kubectl create, kubectl scale, 
                  kubectl expose (quick for exploration)

      Declarative: kubectl apply -f file.yaml 
                   (the production/GitOps way — what Skupper v2 uses heavily)

  * Every Kubernetes object has:

        - metadata (name, namespace, labels, annotations)

        - spec (desired state)

        - status (observed state — usually read-only)

  * Namespaces are your friend for isolation while learning.

  * kubectl is your primary interface to the API server.

